text.section:
The driver of a vehicle shall yield the right-of-way to:
A blind or partially blind pedestrian using a guide dog or carrying a cane predominantly white or metallic in color (with or without a red tip);
A deaf or hearing impaired pedestrian accompanied by a guide dog; or
A mobility impaired individual crossing a roadway while using any of the following mobility-assisted devices:
A manual or motorized wheelchair;
A motorized scooter;
Crutches; or
A cane.
